result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

clerked by SM
Defendant Douglas W Moses in court with attorney Lauren O. Otto.  Angela Lynn Beranek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
14CF126, 14CF215, 14CF250, 14CT68, 14TR284, 14TR511 & 14TR512. Agreement reached.

State puts agreement on record:
14CT68 - Plead guilty to OWI 3rd.  State moves to dismiss companion charge and 14TR284  .382 BAC nonaggravated.
$3,976.00 fine, 110 days jail, 30 months driver's license revocation and 30 months ignition interlock.
14CF126 - Plead guilty to OWI 4th.  State moves to dismiss and read-in PAC charge along with 14TR511 & 14TR512.  State requests  PSI.
14CF215 - Dismiss and Read-In.  
14CF250 -Plead guilty.  State requests PSI.
Court questions Attorney Otto and Court questions Defendant.

14CT68 - Defendant pleads guilty to OWI 3rd.  Court accepts and finds guilty.  Court dismisses remaining counts and reads-in along with 14TR284.
14CF126 - Defendant pleads guilty to OWI 4th.  Court accepts and finds guilty.  Court dismisses and reads-in count 2 , 14TR511 & 14TR512.
14CF250 - Defendant pleads guilty to felony bail jumping.  Court accepts and finds guilty.  
14CF126 &14CF250 - Court order PSI.  State requests bond be revoked.  Attorney Otto objects.  State withdraws request to revoke bond.
14CF215 - State moves to dismiss and read-in entire case.  Court grants.
14CT68 - Court orders 110 days jail with good time, huber and work release privileges to begin today 10/22/2014 at 4 PM.  $3,976.00 fine inclusive of all costs - 60 days to pay.  AODA and complete driver safety plan.  30 months revocation of driver's license and 30 months ignition interlock device.   Court grants one-half price IID.  

Bond remains in effect for other cases pending.
CLERK NOTE:  TR CASES ARE DISMISSED AND READ-IN FOR PURPOSES OF CONSIDERATION IN SENTENCING ON 14CF126 & 14CF250.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 5, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Plea hearing on October 22, 2014 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant Douglas W Moses in court with attorney Lauren O. Otto.  Russell E. Berg appeared for the State of Wisconsin. THIS COVERS 14CF250 AND 14CF215. 

14CF250: Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing. Court accepts Defendant's waiver, finds probable cause and binds over for trial. Information filed. Defendant waives formal reading and pleads NG.

14CF215: Defendant waives formal reading and pleads NG to both counts.

Both cases set for 9/17/14 at 2:00 p.m. to track with other cases.

Bond continues.  Plea hearing scheduled for September 17, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
